{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:Q$objc(cs)NSArray","text":"NSArray<MLNPolygon *>"},{"kind":"text","text":" * "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"interiorPolygons"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The area occupied by any interior polygons is excluded from the overall shape."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Interior polygons should not overlap. An interior polygon should not have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interior polygons of its own."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If there are no interior polygons, the value of this property is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNPolygon(py)interiorPolygons","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"interiorPolygons"}],"symbolKind":"property","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"interiorPolygons"}],"title":"interiorPolygons","roleHeading":"Instance Property","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The array of polygons nested inside the receiver."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon\/interiorpolygons"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"]]},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documen